-- Cloud marketing firm Vocus explores sale- sources
-- 
-- Wed Mar 12, 2014 04:06PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, March 12 (Reuters) - Vocus Inc <VOCS.O>, a provider of cloud marketing software, is looking to sell itself and has attracted interest from industry rivals and private equity firms, according to several people familiar with the matter.

Online marketing company ConstantContact, web services company Web.com Group Inc <WWWW.O> and private equity firm GTCR are among the parties interested in buying Vocus, one of the people said.